<HEAD>
<TITLE>Medical Innovation Project -- PFF</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000">
<map name="wst">
<area shape="rect" coords="0,0,92,20" href="#works">
<area shape="rect" coords="93,0,193,20" href="#speeches">
<area shape="rect" coords="194,0,318,20" href="#testimonies"></map>

<ul><blockquote>

<a href="welcome.html"><img src="bi.gif" align="right" border="0" alt="PFF"></a>
<center>
<a href="wst.map"><img src="wst.gif" border="0" USEMAP="#wst" ISMAP></a>
<img src="miphead.gif" alt="Medical Innovation Project">
</center>
<br><br><P>
<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="20%">
Surgical Lasers!  Genetic Engineering!  Molecular Transports!
 Surgery in Cyberspace!  Civilization is poised to make major
strides in medicine and health.  These advances have the potential
to dramatically increase both life spans and the quality of life,
while at the same time reducing the cost of health care.
<P>
Yet America's enjoyment of these benefits is threatened because
every day the current system for approving new medical technology
stays in place is another day Americans die needless deaths and
suffer senseless pain.   Why is that many of our drug and medical
device companies are able to offer products to patients in Europe
years before they ever receive FDA approval to do in the USA?
 How do we speed the approval process while ensuring safety? 
Who should pay for all this?  Is it time to replace the FDA?
<td valign="top">
<a name="works"></a>
<img src="bullet.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><big>Works</big>
<ul>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="/pff/mip/len051496.html">Real Reform or Pilot Programs?</a>
 by Thomas Lenard.<br>
