<center><a href="people.map"><img src="i-people.gif" border="0" align="top" ISMAP USEMAP="#people"></a></center>
<h1>Board of Directors</h1>
<p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/keyworth.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of George Keyworth" src="/pff/multi/people/keyworth.gif"></a><b><a name="Keyworth">George A. (Jay) Keyworth, II, Ph.D.</a></b>
<ul>Keyworth is the chairman of the board, senior fellow and cofounder of the
Foundation.  He served as science advisor to 
<a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/president/reagan.html">President Ronald Reagan</a>
and prior to that was director of the 
<a href="http://mentor.lanl.gov/Welcome.html">physics division</a>
at 
<a href="http://www.lanl.gov">Los Alamos National Laboratory</a>
in 
<a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional_Information/States/New_Mexico/">New Mexico.</a>
</ul><p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/eisenach.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of Jeffrey Eisenach" src="/pff/multi/people/eisenach.gif"></a><b><a name="Eisenach">Jeffrey A. Eisenach, Ph.D.</a></b>
<ul>President, senior fellow, and co-founder of the Foundation,
Eisenach served as a senior economist at the <a href="http://www.ftc.gov/>Federal Trade
Commission</a> and in the Reagan administration's
<a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/White_House/EOP/html/other/OMB.html">Office of Management and Budget.</a> 
He has also worked at the
American Enterprise Institute, the <a href="/heritage">Heritage Foundation</a>
and the Hudson Institute.</ul><p>


<p>
<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/hanna.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of Frank Hanna" src="/pff/multi/people/hanna.gif"></a><b><a name="Hanna">Frank J. Hanna III</a></b>
<ul>Chairman of the Foundation's
Committee for American Progress, Hanna is the chief executive
officer of HBR Capital, a merchant banking fund.  Prior to
his 
<a href="http://riskweb.bus.utexas.edu/finweb.html">investment work,</a>
Hanna practiced 
<a href="http://www.law.cornell.edu/topical.html">corporate law.</a>  
He also created a 
television program called "One Room Schoolhouse," aimed at
helping parents become more active in their children's education.</ul>

<p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/huffingt.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of Arianna Huffington" src="/pff/multi/people/huffingt.gif"></a><b><a name="Huffington">Arianna Huffington</a></b>
<ul>Huffington is a well-known and noted author, lecturer and broadcaster.  She has
written books on a broad range of topics, from the
<a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/cheryb/women/wshome.html">feminist movement</a>
to a biography of Pablo Picasso.  She frequently
makes guest appearances on a number of national television
programs and is often asked to speak on 
<a href="http://www.msstate.edu/Fineart_Online/art-resources.html">art</a>
and culture,
humanism and 
<a href="http://www.protree.com/Spirit.html">spiritualism.</a></ul>

<p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/lubbers.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of Mark Lubbers" src="/pff/multi/people/lubbers.gif"></a><b><a name="Lubbers">R. Mark Lubbers</a></b>
<ul>Lubbers is senior vice president of
corporate affairs for the Associated Group, a family
of insurance and financial services companies with
headquarters in 
<a href="http://www.iquest.net/Q95/">Indianapolis.</a>
Prior to that, Lubbers was 
senior vice president of the Hudson Institute.  He also
served as senior executive assistant to 
<a href="http://www.state.in.us/">Indiana</a> Gov. Robert Orr
and as a legislative assistant to Sen. Richard
Lugar, R-Ind.</ul>
<p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/miller.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of James Miller" src="/pff/multi/people/miller.gif"></a><b><a name="Miller">James C. Miller III</a></b>
<ul>Miller serves as counselor to both Citizens for
a Sound Economy and the Tax Foundation.  He is a distinguished
fellow at the Center for the Study of Public Choice at George
Mason University, a member of the Administrative Conference of
the United States, and a senior fellow (by courtesy) of the
<a href="http://hoover.stanford.edu">Hoover Institution.</a>
Miller was director of the 
<a href="gopher://sunny.stat-usa.gov/11/BUDGETFY95">Office
of Management and Budget</a> from 1985 through 1988.  Involved
in a number of business endeavors, Miller frequently appears
in the national media to discuss public issues.  In 1994,
Miller unsuccessfully ran for the 
<a href="http://www.berkeleyic.com/conservative/">Republican</a> 
nomination to the 
<a href="http://www.infi.net/pilot/senate/">U.S. Senate from Virginia.</a>
</ul><p>

<dt><a href="/pff/multi/people/roesing.jpg"><img hspace="8" alt="Picture of William Roesing" src="/pff/multi/people/roesing.gif"></a><b><a name="Roesing">William P. Roesing</a></b>
<ul>Vice President for public
policy at Joseph E. Seagram & Sons, Inc., Roesing heads the
company's 
<a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/White_House/EOP/html/DC_map.html">Washington, D.C.</a> 
office.  Prior to joining Seagram,
he served as a strategic consultant to a broad spectrum of
political leaders and corporations.</ul>


<p>
