<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Advancing Medical Innovation: Contents -- PFF</TITLE></HEAD><BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/pff/notebook.gif" LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000"> <ul><blockquote><a href="/pff"><img src="/pff/pffdoc.gif" align="right" border="0"></a>
<h2>Advancing Medical Innovation:<br>
Health, Safety, and the Role of Government in the 21st Century</h2>

You can 
<ul>
<li><a href="fda.exe">Download</a> the self-extracting .zip Word 6.0 for IBM (250k) for viewing off-line
<li>Read the <a href="exec.html"><B>Executive Summary</B></a>, or
<li>Use the Table of Contents Below to navigate through the full report.
</ul>

<center><h3>TABLE OF CONTENTS</h3></center>
<br>
<a href="fm.html"><B>Front Matter and Acknowledgements</B></a>
<P>
<a href="intro.html"><B>Introduction and Summary</B></a>
<ul><a href="biologic.html">Drugs and Biologics</a>
<br><a href="devices.html">Medical Devices</a>
</ul>
<BR>
<B>Chapter 1:</B>   <a href="1.html">Institutional Alternatives for the Regulation of Drugs and Medical Devices</a>, by Robert D. Tollison<BR>
<ul>Appendix:  <a href="1-app.html">The Private Monopoly Laboratory</a>
</ul><BR>
<B>Chapter 2: </B> Therapeutic Drugs and Biologics, by Henry I. Miller and William M. Wardell<BR>
<ul><a href="2.html">Executive Summary and Introduction</a><br>
<a href="2a.html">Regulatory Reform:  Importance, History, and Goals</a><br>
<a href="2b.html">The Proposed New System:  Regulation of Drugs and Biologics</a><br>
<a href="2c.html">Achieving the Goals of Reform</a><br>
Appendix:  <a href="2-app.html">Drug Development and Regulation:  The Current System</a>
</ul><BR>
<B>Chapter 3: </B> Medical Devices, by Ralph A. Epstein<BR>
<ul><a href="3.html">Executive Summary</a><br>
<a href="3a.html">An Overview of the Medical Device Industry</a><br>
<a href="3b.html">Development of Regulation of the Medical Device Industry</a><br>
<a href="3c.html">The Current State of the Medical Device Industry</a><br>
<a href="3d.html">Current Trends in Reform Proposals</a><br>
<a href="3e.html">The EU Approval System of New Medical Devices</a><br>
<a href="3f.html">A New Regulatory Reform Proposal</a>
</ul>
<br>
<B>Chapter 4:</B>  Regulatory Reform and Liability for Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices, by W. Kip Viscusi<BR>
<ul><a href="4.html">Executive Summary and Introduction</a><br>
<a href="4a.html">The Current Regulatory Structure and its Implications for Tort Liability</a><br>
<a href="4b.html">The Role of Tort Law</a><br>
<a href="4c.html">Legal Implications of a Revised Approval Process</a><br>
<a href="4d.html">Conclusion</a>
</ul>
